		<div id="post_message_1462569">Maledict,<br />
yup, common problem across politics: thinking with the electoral penis <img src="images/smilies/wink.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Wink" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
And note: I'm all for mercy and help for genuine folk, folk who make mistakes...not out right scumbags, in regards to my semi-rant on violent criminals.<br />
<br />
You can only make <i>one </i>mistake, one plea for leniency and help when it comes to serious violence, because you cannot undo that damage. <br />
It's not like self-harm, even though they often spring from the same causes. Your life is your own, but you have no right to unwarrantedly brutalize and terrorize others.<br />
And you have to realize some folk are just throughly evil, you can't help folk like that.<br />
<br />
As said previously: twice here in Scotland, rampant violent crime was stamped out by ye proverbial &quot;Hanging judges&quot;, who doled out 10+ year sentences for violent crime, and hiring big Highlanders as cops and telling them to &quot;Put the boot in&quot; on scumbags. Not very nice, but it worked.<br />
it doesn't stop the problem though, only temporarily gets it off the streets.<br />
<a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/scotland/5063092.stm" target="_blank">http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/uk_news/scotland/5063092.stm</a><br />
<br />
We need a complete change in the way our societies work, but fat chance. too many sleeks and psychos think mercy, kindess, sharing etc are excuses for them to get away with anything, and are &quot;weak&quot;.<br />
We need such folk either excised from society completely, top to bottom, or treated (if mental cases, which most are, but our current medical and psychological ability to treat such is woeful).<br />
Do that and you'd remove much of the havoc that breeds more of the same ratbags, ad infinitum. That's why it keeps recurring.<br />
Keeps leading to cycles of violence, abuse and even war.<br />
<br />
hence as I've repeatedly said, education is about the best way to deal with our Human woes...and the real SOBs need FUBARed to drain their poison out of their societies to let the former work.<br />
<br />
My cousin's thinking about beoming a social worker dealing with addiction, as that's alas, what he's had experience with, good luck to him, hope he can help many others <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smilie" class="inlineimg" /></div>
