</div>The problem with XTC is that it does not always work within the same timeframe. This makes people think they had a &quot;bad pill&quot; and take another because the effects did not kick in within the 5 minutes after taking it (effects can kick in even an hour later) Thereby they overheat their system and these people die from an overdose.<br />
 <br />
 <br />
Pot/Marihuana is a relaxation drug, overuse causes brain damage and let people react slowly. Users and addicts are not the type to overheat and go for violence.</div>
		<!-- / message -->

		

		

		
