		<!-- message -->
		<div id="post_message_1462636">There are 2 fallacies that are repeated over and over in the drug debate, including here:<br />
<br />
1) Pot is a &quot;gateway drug&quot; . There is not a realistic shread of evidence to support this. NONE. Got that? NONE. Sure, folks that do hard drugs probably smoked pot at some point...they also drank milk...There is NO scientific cause and effect at work here. If there is Any tenuous connection, it is that their Dealers sell everything...remove the dealers from pot sales (by legalization), remove all connection.<br />
<br />
 DARE and Partnership For A Drug-Free America LIE, to everyones' detriment.<br />
<br />
2) Legalization will be a moneymaker. It will Not. Folks will grow their own, and trade with friends. The only increase in funds will be taxes on the sale of stuff to grow your own weed...Sure, there will be some societal Savings, by not wasting our criminal rescource system by prosecuting something that should have been legalized in 1970, but that is it. Some side-effects are good, such as not having pot dealers take up prison space that ought to be reserved for killers and rapists...<br />
<br />
Pot would have to be cigarette cheap to be able to tax it to make money, do we really want that? (You could start low, getting folks out of the habit of growing their own, and slowly, but continuously raising the tax, but our government isn't that smart...)</div>
		<!-- / message -->

		

		

		

		

		

